airs. Tax payers may also mail in payments, pay at most County banks, or cash payments", "may be made at the Treasurer\u2019s office in the Historic Courthouse in Pontiac.", "Payments using a credit or debit card or E-check may also be made on the County\u2019s website,", "www.livingstoncountyil.gov, on the Treasurer\u2019s page. The credit card companies do charge a 2.25%", "convenience fee and the fee will appear separately on both your receipt and monthly statement. The", "fee for processing an E-check is a flat rate of $2.00.", "Payments paid after the due dates will result in a 1.5% penalty per month on each installment. The", "late payment schedule is printed on the tax stubs of the bill.", "After September 14th, payments will not be accepted at area banks and MUST be made directly to the", "Treasurer\u2019s office. Personal checks will not be accepted after October 18, 2021 and payment after", "that date must be made with a cashier\u2019s check, money order, credit card, or cash. Delinquent Notices", "will be mailed on approximately October 18, 2021. The names of delinquent property owners will be", "published in the local newspapers during the week of October 25, 2021. Online payments using a", "credit or debit card will be accepted up through Friday, November 5, 2021. The annual tax sale will be", "held on Monday, November 15, 2021.", "Several items are printed on the reverse side of the tax bill which may answer most taxpayer", "questions. For further information please call between 8:00 A.M. and 4:30 P.M. Monday-Friday:", "Payment questions \u2013 Treasurer\u2019s office - 815-844-2306", "Assessment Questions/Name or Address Changes \u2013 Assessor\u2019s office \u2013 815-844-7214", "Tax rates/Prior Year Redemptions \u2013 County Clerk \u2013 815-844-2006"], "bbox": [[0.129412, 0.091169, 0.773254, 0.015573], [0.129412, 0.107074, 0.768671, 0.015573], [0.12943, 0.123132, 0.6416120000000001, 0.015573], [0.12943, 0.155095, 0.796271, 0.015573], [0.129448, 0.1